A system administrator has successfully installed the WebSphereApplication Server
Network Deployment core product. The administrator then attempts to start server1, and it
fails to start. On initial inspection, the administrator finds that the profiles directory is empty.
What should the administrator do next?
A. Start the node agent for server1.
B. Inspect the SystemOut.log file of server1.
C. Run the Installation Verification Tool (IVT).
D. Run the WebSphere Customization Toolbox.
Answer: D

A. Execute the pmt script from a remote machine.

C. Edit the server.xml file on <machine_a>to change ports.
